%S A273091 6,45,2475,2175,5775,5075,13475,15925,2975,2730,510,468,396,348,924,
%T A273091 812,2156,2548,476,28,210,1575,225,12375,10875,28875,25375,67375,
%U A273091 79625,14875,13650,2550,2340,1980,1740,4620,4060,10780,12740,2380,2184,408,152,92,380,230,950,575,2375,9625
%N A273091 Successive integers produced by Conway's PRIMEGAME, starting with 6 rather than 2.
%C A273091 Upon reaching a(22) = 225 = A185242(33) = A007542(21), this sequence becomes the same as A007542, having skipped over 4 (which corresponds to the prime 2) and then goes on to 8 (which corresponds to the prime 3).
%F A273091 a(n) = A007542(n-1) = A185242(n+11) for all n > 21. - _M. F. Hasler_, Apr 27 2026
%e A273091 Multiply a(0) = 6 by 15/2 to obtain a(1) = 45. Then for 45, multiplying by the first thirteen fractions fails to produce an integer, so a(2) = 45 * 55 = 2475.
%t A273091 (* First run the program for A203907 to define conwayProc *) NestList[conwayProc, 6, 50]
%o A273091 (Python) A273091_first = lambda N: [(N:=A203907(N) if i else 6) for i in range(N)] # _M. F. Hasler_, Apr 27 2026
%Y A273091 Cf. A203907 (the PRIMEGAME successor map), A007542 (trajectory of 2), A185242 (trajectory of 3).
%K A273091 nonn,easy,changed
%O A273091 0,1
